#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn22.26"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.26:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.26:0.2"
msgid "3. Bhāravagga "
msgstr "3. The Burden "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.26:0.3"
msgid "26. Assādasutta "
msgstr "26. Gratification "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.28, sc1
msgctxt "sn22.26:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: Pubbeva → pubbe (pts1, mr)
#. VAR: bodhisattasseva → bodhisattassa (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn22.26:1.2"
msgid "“Pubbeva me, bhikkhave, sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato etadahosi: "
msgstr "“Mendicants, before my awakening—when I was still unawakened but intent on awakening—I thought: "

msgctxt "sn22.26:1.3"
msgid "‘ko nu kho rūpassa assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇaṃ? "
msgstr "‘What’s the gratification, the drawback, and the escape when it comes to form … "

msgctxt "sn22.26:1.4"
msgid "Ko vedanāya assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇaṃ? "
msgstr "feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.26:1.5"
msgid "Ko saññāya assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇaṃ? "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.26:1.6"
msgid "Ko saṅkhārānaṃ assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇaṃ? "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.26:1.7"
msgid "Ko viññāṇassa assādo, ko ādīnavo, kiṃ nissaraṇan’ti? "
msgstr "and consciousness?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.26:1.8"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, bhikkhave, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me: "

msgctxt "sn22.26:1.9"
msgid "‘yaṃ kho rūpaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, ayaṃ rūpassa assādo. "
msgstr "‘The pleasure and happiness that arise from form: this is its gratification. "

msgctxt "sn22.26:1.10"
msgid "Yaṃ rūpaṃ aniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, ayaṃ rūpassa ādīnavo. "
msgstr "That form is impermanent, suffering, and perishable: this is its drawback. "

msgctxt "sn22.26:1.11"
msgid "Yo rūpasmiṃ chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ, idaṃ rūpassa nissaraṇaṃ. "
msgstr "Removing and giving up desire and greed for form: this is its escape. "

msgctxt "sn22.26:1.12"
msgid "Yaṃ vedanaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, ayaṃ vedanāya assādo. "
msgstr "The pleasure and happiness that arise from feeling … "

#. VAR: Yaṃ → yā (mr)
msgctxt "sn22.26:1.13"
msgid "Yaṃ vedanā aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā, ayaṃ vedanāya ādīnavo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.26:1.14"
msgid "Yo vedanāya chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ, idaṃ vedanāya nissaraṇaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.26:1.15"
msgid "Yaṃ saññaṃ paṭicca uppajjati … pe … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.26:1.16"
msgid "yaṃ saṅkhāre paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, ayaṃ saṅkhārānaṃ assādo. "
msgstr "choices … "

#. VAR: Yaṃ → ye (bj, s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "sn22.26:1.17"
msgid "Yaṃ saṅkhārā aniccā dukkhā vipariṇāmadhammā, ayaṃ saṅkhārānaṃ ādīnavo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.26:1.18"
msgid "Yo saṅkhāresu chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ, idaṃ saṅkhārānaṃ nissaraṇaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.26:1.19"
msgid "Yaṃ viññāṇaṃ paṭicca uppajjati sukhaṃ somanassaṃ, ayaṃ viññāṇassa assādo. "
msgstr "consciousness: this is its gratification. "

msgctxt "sn22.26:1.20"
msgid "Yaṃ viññāṇaṃ aniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, ayaṃ viññāṇassa ādīnavo. "
msgstr "That consciousness is impermanent, suffering, and perishable: this is its drawback. "

msgctxt "sn22.26:1.21"
msgid "Yo viññāṇasmiṃ chandarāgavinayo chandarāgappahānaṃ, idaṃ viññāṇassa nissaraṇaṃ’. "
msgstr "Removing and giving up desire and greed for consciousness: this is its escape.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
#. VAR: abhisambuddho’ti → abhisambuddho (si, s1-3)
msgctxt "sn22.26:2.1"
msgid "Yāvakīvañcāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ pañcannaṃ upādānakkhandhānaṃ evaṃ assādañca assādato ādīnavañca ādīnavato nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ nābbhaññāsiṃ, neva tāvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, ‘sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddho’ti paccaññāsiṃ. "
msgstr "As long as I didn’t truly understand these five grasping aggregates’ gratification, drawback, and escape in this way for what they are, I didn’t announce my supreme perfect awakening in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.26:2.2"
msgid "Yato ca khvāhaṃ, bhikkhave, imesaṃ pañcannaṃ upādānakkhandhānaṃ evaṃ assādañca assādato ādīnavañca ādīnavato nissaraṇañca nissaraṇato yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ; "
msgstr "But when I did truly understand these five grasping aggregates’ gratification, drawback, and escape in this way for what they are, I announced my supreme perfect awakening in this world with its gods, Māras, and Brahmās, this population with its ascetics and brahmins, its gods and humans. "

msgctxt "sn22.26:2.3"
msgid "athāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sadevake loke samārake sabrahmake sassamaṇabrāhmaṇiyā pajāya sadevamanussāya anuttaraṃ sammāsambodhiṃ abhisambuddhoti paccaññāsiṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.26:2.4"
msgid "Ñāṇañca pana me dassanaṃ udapādi: "
msgstr "Knowledge and vision arose in me: "

#. VAR: vimutti → cetovimutti (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn22.26:2.5"
msgid "‘akuppā me vimutti; ayamantimā jāti; natthi dāni punabbhavo’”ti. "
msgstr "‘My freedom is unshakable; this is my last rebirth; now there are no more future lives.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.26:2.6"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

